<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="476" pageId="24" pageNumber="475" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1829,2036]" box="[151,1376,1901,1929]" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1901,1927]" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">Description.</emphasis>
Larva: body length 
<quantity box="[524,613,1902,1929]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="24" pageNumber="475" unit="mm" value="5.2">5.2 mm</quantity>
; caudal filaments 
<quantity box="[815,904,1902,1928]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="24" pageNumber="475" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
. Body color light brown (
<figureCitation box="[1192,1299,1902,1928]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-19@26.[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 18. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.—total view of larva; B.—labrum; C.—hypopharynx; D, E.—mandibles; F.—labium; G.—maxilla. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808383/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">Figs 18A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1311,1363,1902,1928]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-20@27.[151,1436,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.— abdomen; B.—fore leg; C.—middle leg; D.—hind leg; E.—stout setae from dorsal surface of forefemur; F.—tarsal claw; G.—gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808387/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">19A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1829,2036]" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1938,1964]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">Head</emphasis>
: Vertex with pair of well-developed and elongated protuberances. No ocellar protuberances. Inner margin of antennal base with short projections. Frontal shelf not expanded. Genae slightly produced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,1829,2036]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1437,151,2013]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="476" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">
Long hair-like setae present along anterior margin of frontal shelf and sparsely present below compound eye. Clypeus with anterior row of long hair-like setae. Labrum width nearly 2× length (
<figureCitation box="[1100,1204,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-19@26.[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 18. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.—total view of larva; B.—labrum; C.—hypopharynx; D, E.—mandibles; F.—labium; G.—maxilla. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808383/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
), with shallow, very broad notch anteriorly; dorsal face with scattered long, hair-like setae on lateral margin and with several rows of brush-like setae anteriorly; ventral face with simple or fimbriate setae on lateral margins and dense, transverse row of 7–9 long, stout setae. Hypopharynx (
<figureCitation box="[649,749,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-19@26.[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 18. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.—total view of larva; B.—labrum; C.—hypopharynx; D, E.—mandibles; F.—labium; G.—maxilla. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808383/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 18C</figureCitation>
) with superlinguae size subequal to linguae size; lingua with row of short setae on anterior margin; superlingua with row of long, thin setae on margin, with setae decreasing in length anteriorly. Mandibles with lateral setae relatively long (
<figureCitation box="[851,987,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-19@26.[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 18. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.—total view of larva; B.—labrum; C.—hypopharynx; D, E.—mandibles; F.—labium; G.—maxilla. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808383/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 18D, E</figureCitation>
). Maxilla without palp (
<figureCitation box="[1258,1362,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-19@26.[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 18. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.—total view of larva; B.—labrum; C.—hypopharynx; D, E.—mandibles; F.—labium; G.—maxilla. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808383/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 18G</figureCitation>
); apex of galea-lacinia relatively sharp with two incisors, and with few long, stout setae on apex; with two dentisetae and double row of four stout setae. Labium with glossae longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[976,1078,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-19@26.[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 18. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.—total view of larva; B.—labrum; C.—hypopharynx; D, E.—mandibles; F.—labium; G.—maxilla. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808383/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 18F</figureCitation>
), longer than paraglossae; palp segment III elongate, with length/width ratio 2.13–2.15.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis box="[199,280,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Thorax</emphasis>
: Prothorax width subequal to head width, with no anterolateral projections and three pairs of distinct dorsal tubercles; ventral spines absent. Mesonotum with two pairs of distinct, elongated, tubercles between fore wing pads; fore wing pads base darkly pigmented. Dorsal surface of thorax without any bifid or starlike setae. Coxae with slight dorsolateral projections; projections with hair-like setae. All femora slightly flattened (
<figureCitation box="[1285,1424,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-20@27.[151,1436,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.— abdomen; B.—fore leg; C.—middle leg; D.—hind leg; E.—stout setae from dorsal surface of forefemur; F.—tarsal claw; G.—gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808387/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 19B–C</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface of forefemur with incomplete, narrow, transverse band of long, pointed or bluntly pointed, apically stout setae (
<figureCitation box="[288,392,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-20@27.[151,1436,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.— abdomen; B.—fore leg; C.—middle leg; D.—hind leg; E.—stout setae from dorsal surface of forefemur; F.—tarsal claw; G.—gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808387/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 19E</figureCitation>
); outer margin with middle-sized and long, hair-like setae and single chalaza bearing long, stout seta medially; inner margin with middle-sized and long, hair-like setae only; anterior margin with no dorsal projections (
<figureCitation box="[290,392,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-20@27.[151,1436,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.— abdomen; B.—fore leg; C.—middle leg; D.—hind leg; E.—stout setae from dorsal surface of forefemur; F.—tarsal claw; G.—gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808387/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 19B</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface of foretibia with two long, pointed, stout setae; outer margins of foretibia and tarsus with different-sized hair-like setae, most long; inner margins of fore tibia and fore tarsus with short, hair-like setae and row of short and middle-sized spine-like setae; distal end of inner margin of foretibia with group of stout setae. Foretibial projection short. Outer margins of middle and hind femora with several long, pointed, stout setae and different-sized hair-like setae, most long (
<figureCitation box="[669,807,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-20@27.[151,1436,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.— abdomen; B.—fore leg; C.—middle leg; D.—hind leg; E.—stout setae from dorsal surface of forefemur; F.—tarsal claw; G.—gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808387/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 19C, D</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surfaces of middle and hind tibiae with several long, pointed, stout setae. Outer margins of middle and hind tibiae and tarsi with hair-like setae, most long. Inner margins of middle and hind tibiae and tarsi with different-sized spine-like setae. Tarsal claws of all legs each with about 8 denticles and several subapical setae, without distal palisade of denticles (
<figureCitation box="[1069,1168,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-20@27.[151,1436,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.— abdomen; B.—fore leg; C.—middle leg; D.—hind leg; E.—stout setae from dorsal surface of forefemur; F.—tarsal claw; G.—gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808387/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 19F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis box="[199,305,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Gill III brown, semi-operculate, without medial transverse band of weakened membrane (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1423,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-20@27.[151,1436,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.— abdomen; B.—fore leg; C.—middle leg; D.—hind leg; E.—stout setae from dorsal surface of forefemur; F.—tarsal claw; G.—gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808387/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 19G</figureCitation>
); gills IV–VII translucent. Dorsal lamellae of gills IV–VI with small projection on posterior margin. Gills III–VI ventral lamellae bifid, with dorsal and ventral lobules; lobules tips acute. Gills VII narrow, with medial point of attachment to tergum. Terga I and II with long hair-like setae on posterior margins. Terga III–IX with pairs of welldeveloped, bluntly pointed submedian projections (
<figureCitation box="[723,824,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-20@27.[151,1436,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.— abdomen; B.—fore leg; C.—middle leg; D.—hind leg; E.—stout setae from dorsal surface of forefemur; F.—tarsal claw; G.—gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808387/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 19A</figureCitation>
) bear few short and blunt stout setae; those of terga V– VIII most developed; on tergum VIII largest and directed most laterally; tergum IX with pair of short, blunt, median spines and weak, oblique ridges. Tergum X without paired submedian projections. Segments VI–VIII with lateral margins strongly upturned, forming outer portion of prominent gill chamber. Pairs of projections progressively larger posteriorly up to segment VIII and covered with short, blunt stout setae. Abdominal sterna flattened, with no maculation and no long setae. Caudal filaments pale, with dense whorls of long, stout, hair-like setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2013]" box="[199,411,1374,1401]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,278,1374,1400]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Adults</emphasis>
: Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="476" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1410,1436]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Martynov &amp; Selvakumar &amp; Subramanian &amp; Sivaramakrishnan &amp; Vasanth &amp; Sinha &amp; Jacobus, 2021" authorityName="Martynov &amp; Selvakumar &amp; Subramanian &amp; Sivaramakrishnan &amp; Vasanth &amp; Sinha &amp; Jacobus" authorityYear="2021" box="[328,589,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Ephemerellidae" genus="Torleya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simbalbarensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[328,589,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Torleya simbalbarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[595,686,1411,1437]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[595,679,1411,1437]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is easily distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName box="[1072,1245,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Ephemerellidae" genus="Torleya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1072,1157,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Torleya</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: (i) head with two pairs of suboccipital and occipital protuberances, second pair of protuberances well-developed and elongated; (ii) maxilla without palp (
<figureCitation box="[989,1098,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-19@26.[190,1398,181,1957]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 18. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.—total view of larva; B.—labrum; C.—hypopharynx; D, E.—mandibles; F.—labium; G.—maxilla. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808383" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808383/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 18G</figureCitation>
); (iii) tarsal claws of all legs each with about 8 denticles and several subapical setae, without distal palisade of denticles (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1311,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-20@27.[151,1436,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.— abdomen; B.—fore leg; C.—middle leg; D.—hind leg; E.—stout setae from dorsal surface of forefemur; F.—tarsal claw; G.—gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808387/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 19F</figureCitation>
); (iv) terga III–IX with pairs of well-developed, bluntly pointed submedian projections (
<figureCitation box="[1051,1160,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-20@27.[151,1436,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 19. Larva of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov., holotype. A.— abdomen; B.—fore leg; C.—middle leg; D.—hind leg; E.—stout setae from dorsal surface of forefemur; F.—tarsal claw; G.—gill III." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808387" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808387/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 19A</figureCitation>
); those of terga V–VIII most developed; on tergum VIII largest and directed most laterally; tergum IX with pair of short, blunt, median spines and weak; (v) setation of femora; (vi) shape of gill III.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1413,1663,1689]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2013]" box="[199,1413,1663,1689]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1663,1689]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after the 
<typeStatus box="[692,740,1663,1689]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">type</typeStatus>
locality, Simbalbara Wildlife Sanctuary, 
<collectingRegion box="[1201,1409,1663,1689]" country="India" name="Himachal Pradesh" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Himachal Pradesh</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="476" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2013]" box="[199,425,1698,1725]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1698,1724]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,420,1699,1725]" name="India" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1734,1760]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Habitat.</emphasis>
Fast flowing stream, with sand and cobble bottom, in Sal (
<taxonomicName authority="Roth" authorityName="Roth" box="[1046,1294,1735,1762]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Shorea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis box="[1046,1224,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Shorea robusta</emphasis>
Roth
</taxonomicName>
) (
<taxonomicName box="[1324,1432,1735,1761]" class="Magnoliopsida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">Malvales</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[151,349,1771,1798]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dipterocarpaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Dipterocarpaceae</taxonomicName>
) forest (
<figureCitation box="[442,547,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1070,1094]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1043]" captionTargetId="figure-19@28.[151,1436,181,1046]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 20. Habitats of Torleya simbalbarensis Selvakumar, Subramanian, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov. (A), Serratella palatovi Martynov, Selvakumar &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov. (B, C) and Torleya dibruensis Selvakumar, Martynov &amp; Jacobus, sp. nov. (D). A.—stream in Simbalbara Wildlife Sanctuary, Sirmour District, Himachal Pradesh, India; B.—stream-main source of the Klang Phat River, Chom Thong District, Chiang Mai Province, Thailand; C.—stream in Tale Valley, Lower Subansiri District, Arunachal Pradesh, India; D.—Dibru River, Papum Pare District, Arunachal Pradesh, India." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4808393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4808393/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="476" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1807,1833]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Remarks.</emphasis>
Notably, 
<taxonomicName authority="Martynov &amp; Selvakumar &amp; Subramanian &amp; Sivaramakrishnan &amp; Vasanth &amp; Sinha &amp; Jacobus, 2021" authorityName="Martynov &amp; Selvakumar &amp; Subramanian &amp; Sivaramakrishnan &amp; Vasanth &amp; Sinha &amp; Jacobus" authorityYear="2021" box="[426,688,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Ephemerellidae" genus="Torleya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simbalbarensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[426,688,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Torleya simbalbarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[695,787,1807,1833]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[695,781,1807,1833]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has no distinct distal palisade of denticles on tarsal claw, which usually is present on other Asian species of the genus; however, it is possible the claws might be worn (Jacobus 
<emphasis box="[256,312,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">et al.</emphasis>
2004).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gui, Zhou &amp; Su" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[199,421,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Ephemerellidae" genus="Torleya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longforceps">
<emphasis box="[199,421,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Torleya longforceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[489,564,1915,1941]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Fujian</collectingRegion>
, in far eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[727,794,1915,1941]" name="China" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gui, H. &amp; Zhou, C. - F. &amp; Su, C. - R." box="[808,981,1915,1941]" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" refId="ref14572" refString="Gui, H., Zhou, C. - F. &amp; Su, C. - R. (1999) Ephemeroptera. In: Huang, B. - K. (Ed.), Fujian Insect Fauna. Vol. 1. Fujian Science &amp; Technology Press, Fuzhou, pp. 324 - 346." type="book" year="1999">
Gui 
<emphasis box="[859,915,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
), is the only species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lestage" authorityYear="1917" box="[1241,1326,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Ephemerellidae" genus="Torleya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1241,1326,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="476">Torleya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
unknown in the larval stage, and we consider it unlikely (based on biogeography) to be conspecific with this new species, which is unknown as alates.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
